{"word":"ἐλαία","slug":"ἐλαία","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ἐλαία, ας, ἡ</el></b> [Attic <el>ἐλάα</el>, <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ etym.\">etym.</a> unknown]<b><p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>1.</pp> olive tree <a href='B:520 11:17'>Ro 11:17</a>, <a href='B:520 11:24'>24</a>; <a href='B:730 11:4'>Rv 11:4</a>;</b> and <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ oft.\">oft.</a> in the gospels in the phrase <el>τὸ <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ὄρος\">ὄρος</a></el> (<el>τὸ ϰαλούμενον</el>) <el>τῶν ἐλαιῶν</el> the Mount of Olives <b><a href='B:470 21:21'>Mt 21:21</a></b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ al.\">al.</a> <b><p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>2.</pp></b> by metonymy, the fruit <b>olive <a href='B:660 3:12'>Js 3:12</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ἔλαθον\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ἔλαιον\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}